The paper deals with lower bounds and upper bounds for static data structures, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The technique developed in the paper is a new approach to proving cell-probe lower bounds, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the separation between polynomial and near linear space, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of RAM algorithms and external memory suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with time-space trade-offs, which is a topic in algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL).
